  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Tear the <strong>ciabatta rolls</strong> up into bite-size pieces and add them to a baking tray</p><p>Drizzle them with <strong>olive oi</strong>l and season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put them in the oven for 10-12 min or until crispy</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/270_step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/270_step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/270_step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/270_step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/270_step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and cut the<strong> red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into wedges, then separate the layers into 'petals'</p><p>Deseed the <strong>green pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Cut the <strong>tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> into wedges</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/270_step-2pepper-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/270_step-2pepper-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/270_step-2pepper-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/270_step-2pepper-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/270_step-2pepper-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large pan wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid, with 1-2 tbsp <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> onion</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>water</strong> and cook, covered, for 3 min</p><p>Remove the lid and add the<strong> sliced green pepper</strong></p><p>Cook, covered, for a further 10 min or until browned (add a little water if too dry)</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/270_step-3pepper-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/270_step-3pepper-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/270_step-3pepper-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/270_step-3pepper-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/270_step-3pepper-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the<strong> tomatoes</strong> to a separate baking tray</p><p>Add the <strong>feta</strong> to the same tray</p><p>Sprinkle both with<strong> dried oregano</strong> and bake for 5 min, or until the feta is hot and softened</p>",
